Payne Zero attribution notice
=============================

Payne Zero is a modern reimplementation of a one-dimensional local thermodynamic equilibrium (LTE) stellar-atmosphere and spectrum calculation. Its scientific lineage includes the Kurucz atmosphere, synthesis, and line-data work, whose numerical conventions remain important for comparison and reproducibility. Payne Zero is not a wrapper around the historical programs. Please cite the relevant Kurucz publications when those methods or data contribute to an analysis.

The immediate implementation and validation lineage is pyKurucz:

Elliot M. Kim and Yuan-Sen Ting, pyKurucz: A Pure Python Reimplementation of Kurucz ATLAS12 and SYNTHE for Self-Consistent Stellar Atmospheres and Spectra (2026), https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11693

pyKurucz is MIT licensed, copyright (c) 2026 Elliot M. Kim and Yuan-Sen Ting.

The representative APOGEE line-spread-function builder follows the public jobovy/apogee implementation, copyright (c) 2013 Jo Bovy, distributed under the BSD 3-Clause License. APOGEE survey products are provided by SDSS. The solar and Arcturus calibration overlays were derived from the NSO/Kitt Peak solar FTS atlas and the Hinkle, Wallace & Livingston Arcturus atlas. A small excerpt of the Livingston & Wallace (1991) NSO/Kitt Peak solar center-of-disk FTS atlas is included with the physical line-calibration example. The remaining distributed calibration products contain fitted corrections rather than atlas spectra.

Payne Zero-authored source code and generated model products are covered by the repository LICENSE. Upstream programs, catalogs, tables, and survey products retain their original attribution and terms.
